<h3>Dijkstra's Algorithm</h3>
<p>Dijkstra's algorithm is a way of creating a spanning tree that gives the shortest paths from the starting node to every other node in the graph.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>So for example, if we are creating a Dijkstra spanning tree using node C as our starting node, the tree will contain the shortest connections to nodes A, B, D, E, F...</p>
